Obstacle Avoiding Robot using Arduino
📌 Overview

The Obstacle Avoiding Robot is an intelligent autonomous vehicle built using the Arduino Uno R3. It is capable of detecting obstacles in its path and navigating around them without human intervention.

This project demonstrates the fundamental concept of autonomous navigation, widely used in robotics, self-driving vehicles, and industrial automation systems.

🎯 Objectives
To design an autonomous robot capable of avoiding obstacles
To understand sensor-based navigation systems
To implement real-time decision-making using a microcontroller
To gain practical knowledge of embedded systems and robotics
🔧 Components Required
Arduino Uno R3
HC-SR04 Ultrasonic Sensor (3 units)
L298N Motor Driver
DC Gear Motors (BO Motors)
4WD Robot Chassis
18650 Li-ion Batteries & Holder
Jumper Wires
Breadboard
Switch
⚙️ System Architecture

The system consists of three main parts:

Sensing Unit – Ultrasonic sensors detect obstacles
Processing Unit – Arduino processes sensor data
Actuation Unit – Motors controlled via motor driver
🔌 Circuit Connections
Power Supply
Battery (+) → Switch → L298N (+12V)
Battery (–) → L298N GND
L298N 5V → Arduino 5V
L298N GND → Arduino GND
Motor Connections
OUT1 & OUT2 → Left Motors
OUT3 & OUT4 → Right Motors
Motor Control Pins (Arduino → L298N)
IN1 → Pin 8
IN2 → Pin 9
IN3 → Pin 10
IN4 → Pin 11
Sensor Connections
Front Sensor → Trig (6), Echo (7)
Left Sensor → Trig (2), Echo (3)
Right Sensor → Trig (4), Echo (5)
🧠 Working Principle

The robot continuously scans its environment using three ultrasonic sensors.

If front distance > safe limit → moves forward
If obstacle detected → stops
Compares left and right distances
Moves in the direction with more space
If blocked from all sides → reverses and turns

This ensures smooth and collision-free navigation.
